    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras are positioned for a high-ceiling offensive output today, anchored by **Yordan Alvarez** and **Trea Turner**. **Yordan Alvarez** (82.97) stands as our premier play, benefiting from a massive 16% park adjustment and a favorable matchup against Young. His elite xwOBA of 0.393, combined with his placement in the #2 hole, provides the optimal environment for run production. Meanwhile, **Trea Turner** (73.57) remains a high-floor start despite a slight efficiency penalty due to Houser\u2019s quick release to the plate; his #1 lineup positioning and aggressive base-running profile make him essential for our scarcity-driven strategy in stolen bases. **Kyle Schwarber** (71.28) also draws a strong projection, utilizing an elite 0.402 xwOBA to maximize his efficiency against Houser, further reinforcing our power-heavy approach today.\n\nIn the middle of the order, **Colt Keith** (62.32) and **Kazuma Okamoto** (59.99) round out our core, with **Keith** enjoying a significant bump due to his promotion to the #3 spot. **Kazuma Okamoto** narrowly misses the 60-point threshold but remains a start due to the 12% SP skill advantage provided by the matchup against Ober. **Carson Benge** (59.55) captures our final UTIL slot; while his #7 position provides a slight downward pressure on his score, his strong SP skill adjustment against Mikolas keeps him above our replacement threshold. \n\nThe most difficult roster decision today was benching **Jerar Encarnacion** (39.79). Despite an attractive platoon advantage against the left-handed S\u00e1nchez, his low batting order placement and a sub-par 3.02 xERA matchup for the opposition pushed his efficiency score just below our strict 40.0 floor. With **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, **Junior Caminero**, and **Caleb Durbin** all off the schedule, we are effectively managing our game-cap exposure by limiting exposure to the bottom-third of the order. We will continue to monitor the weather and late lineup shuffles, but as it stands, our primary concern remains **Trea Turner** navigating the catcher's pop time against Houser; otherwise, the Zebras are set for a robust day at the plate.",
